    "comment": "Rationale: In fig 2 the authors localize epsin 1 to presynaptic coated pits. In fig 3/4 they inject function blocking antibodies recognizing epsin 1 into the pre synapse.This leads to a massive reduction in the number of SVs following a 5 Hz 30 min stimulation. In fig. 4 they use EM to demonstrate a change in the morphology of clathrin-coated pits.\n\n10/10/2017 Pim\n- I have added Fig.6 to the referenced figures that show effect of anti-epsin antibodies.. Experimental description: by using the lamprey reticulospinal synapse as a model system",
